reviewText: Sure it's from 34 years ago but you really see a band that pushes the limits of a 3 man band and why they are still beloved to this day.  It's an amazing show by a youthful ZZ Top in contrast to the now older and more reserved ZZ Top. Reserved but still great! Billy and Dusty really put such energy into each song and I wonder how much English the German audience understands.  The Little Old Band from Texas in Germany?  Yep, it works just fine.  Wow, what a show!
summary: ZZ Top's best recorded concert ever

reviewText: WOW - I was not a fan of ZZ Top in the early years, but over the years they have definitely become one of my favorites and this DVD is absolutely the best.

reviewText: I love this DVD for many reasons.  The filming is well done.  The sound is great.  If you're a musician, you can see and learn how they played those classic riffs.  This is ZZ Top in their prime when they had a lot of spunk!  Buy it!

reviewText: These guys just flat out rock the German Rockpalast house down.  This concert showcases the band's "Deguello" album (their best, imo) prior to their MTV video "Eliminator" days, which while still good tunes, does not kick ass like tunes such as "I"m Bad, I'm Nationwide", "Cheap Sunglasses", or "Hi-Fi Mama".  I much prefer this DVD to the Live in Texas one that came out later in their career.  Highest Recommendation!!
